{"word":"H5737 - עֲדַר - ʻădar - aw-dar' - Dig","slug":"H5737","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עֲדַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻădar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-dar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dig"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05D3;&#x05E8; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;dar</b> - <i>aw-dar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>arrange</i>, as a battle, a vineyard (to <i>hoe</i>); hence to <i>muster</i>, and so to <i>miss</i> (or find <i>wanting</i>): - dig, fail, keep (rank), lack."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5738\">H5738</a>, <a href=\"#/H5739\">H5739</a>, <a href=\"#/H5740\">H5740</a>, <a href=\"#/H5742\">H5742</a>"}]}